INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS
=========================

This version of SIMCAN works with OMNeT++ 4.6 and INET 2.6-b673687

1) Install OMNeT++ 4.6 (you can download it from http://www.omnetpp.org/omnetpp)
	E.g. $HOME/YOUR_PATH/omnetpp-4.6

2) Install INET 2.6 (you can download it from http://inet.omnetpp.org/index.php?n=Main.Download)
	E.g. $HOME/YOUR_PATH/omnetpp-4.6/projects/inet

3) Extract the downloaded tarball into a directory of your choice
	E.g. $HOME/YOUR_PATH/omnetpp-4.6/projects/simcan

4) Add the following environment variables to ".bashrc" or ".profile" if you want to compile 
   SIMCAN from a command-line console

	export omnetpp_root=$HOME/YOUR_PATH/omnetpp-4.6
	export INET_HOME=$omnetpp_root/projects/inet
	export SIMCAN_HOME=$omnetpp_root/projects/simcan
	export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$omnetpp_root/lib:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
	export PATH=omnetpp_root/bin:$PATH

5) Import the SIMCAN project in OMNeT++ 

	5.1) Open the OMNeT++ IDE
  	5.2) File -> Import -> Existing projects into Workspace
	5.3) Locate the SIMCAN folder and click “Finish” (Do NOT check the "Copy projects into 
	     workspace" checkBox)

6) Add the reference to INET

	6.1) Right click on SIMCAN (Project explorer)
	6.2) Click on Properties -> Project References -> inet checkBox

7) Compile SIMCAN
	
	7.1a) Compile SIMCAN using the IDE (Right click on SIMCAN and click on Build Project) or
	7.1b) Compile SIMCAN from a command-line console.
		$HOME/YOUR_PATH/omnetpp-4.6/projects/simcan> make makefiles && make

8) Enjoy! ;)




